 sees Trump ties to \"alt-right\" dystopian ideology |work=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref>-->\n<ref name=\"csmonitor-jonsson\">{{cite web |url=http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2016/0827/Donald-Trump-s-candidacy-and-the-rise-of-the-alt-right-movement |title=Donald Trump's candidacy and the rise of the 'alt-right' movement |first=Patrik |last=Jonsson |accessdate=September 3, 2016 |date=August 27, 2016 |work=Christian Science Monitor}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"NPR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.npr.org/2016/08/26/491452721/the-history-of-the-alt-right |title=What You Need To Know About The Alt-Right Movement |date=August 26, 2016 |work=NPR.org |accessdate=August 27, 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Bibliography'''\n{{refbegin|30em|indent=yes}}\n:{{cite journal |last=Atkinson |first=David C. |year=2018 |title=Charlottesville and the Alt-Right: A Turning Point? |journal=Politics, Groups, and Identities |volume=6 |issue=2 |pages=309\u2013315 |doi=10.1080/21565503.2018.1454330 |ref=harv}}\n\n:{{cite journal |last=Barkun |first=Michael |year=2017 |title=President Trump and the \"Fringe\" |journal=Terrorism and Political Violence |volume=29 |issue=3 |pages=437\u2013443 |doi=10.1080/09546553.2017.1313649 |ref=harv}}\n\n:{{cite journal |last=Gray |first=Phillip W. |year=2018 |title='The Fire Rises': Identity, the Alt-Right and Intersectionality |journal=Journal of Political Ideologies |volume=23 |issue=2 |pages=141\u2013156 |doi=10.1080/13569317.2018.1451228 |ref=harv|doi-access=free }}\n\n:{{cite book |last=Hawley |first=George |year=2016 |title=Right-Wing Critics of American Conservatism |publisher=University Press of Kansas |location=Lawrence |isbn=978-0-7006-2193-4 |ref=harv}}\n\n:{{cite book |last=Hawley |first=George |authormask=3 |title=Making Sense of the Alt-Right |location=New York |publisher=Columbia University Press |year=2017 |isbn=978-0-231-18512-7 |ref=harv}}\n\n:{{cite journal |last=Hofmann-Kuroda |first=Lisa |year=2017 |title=Free Speech and the Alt-Right |journal=Qui Parle: